        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-04-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-04-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="363" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d363">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by Lieutenant General <persName type="from">Alvan
                            C. Gillem, Jr.</persName>, to Generalissimo <persName type="to">Chiang
                            Kai-shek</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-04-05">April 5,
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>You asked that I inform you when Communist members of Field Teams had gone into
                    Manchuria. I am now informed by Mr. Robertson that 40 Communist Team members
                    proceeded to Mukden on 2 April 1946.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>A. C. <hi rend="smallcaps">Gillem, Jr.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
